    • Method Detail

      • saveElementEnvironment

        @Given(value="^I save element (in position \'(.+?)\' in )?\'(.+?)\' in environment variable \'(.+?)\'.$")
public void saveElementEnvironment(String foo,
                                                                                                                                             String position,
                                                                                                                                             String element,
                                                                                                                                             String envVar)
                                                                                                                                      throws Exception
        Save value for future use.

        If element is a jsonpath expression (i.e. $.fragments[0].id), it will be applied over the last httpResponse.

        If element is a jsonpath expression preceded by some other string (i.e. ["a","b",,"c"].$.[0]), it will be applied over this string. This will help to save the result of a jsonpath expression evaluated over previous stored variable.

        Parameters:
        foo - required variable for gherkin in optional parameters
        position - position from a search result
        element - key in the json response to be saved
        envVar - thread environment variable where to store the value
        Throws:
        Exception - the exception

      • setHeaders

        @Given(value="^I set headers:.$")
public void setHeaders(io.cucumber.datatable.DataTable modifications)
                                                  throws Throwable
        Specify a custom map of headers to be added to future requests
        Parameters:
        modifications - DataTable containing the custom set of headers to be added to the requests. Syntax will be: | <key> | <value> | where: key: header key name value: value for tue key for example: if we want to add the header "token" with value "12345678", to the request header the modification will be: | token | 12345678 |
        Throws:
        Throwable - the throwable
